\int_C \sin x\, dx + \cos y\, dy
C
x^2+y^2=1
(1,0)
(-1,0)
(-1,0)
(2,3)
x=\cos t
y=\sin t
dx=-\sin tdt
dy=\cos tdt
\int_0^\pi \sin(\cos t)(-\sin t) dt+\int_0^\pi \cos(\sin t)\cos t dt=-\cos(\cos t)+\sin(\sin t)|_0^\pi=0
\overrightarrow{F}(x,y)=(\sin x,\cos y)
\frac{\partial {F_x}}{\partial {y}}-\frac{\partial {F_y}}{\partial {x}}=0
V(x,y)
\nabla V(x,y)=\overrightarrow{F}(x,y)
V(x,y)=-\cos x+\sin y
a=(1,0)
b=(2,3)
C
I=\int_C \sin x\, dx + \cos y\, dy=\int_C\overrightarrow{F}\cdot\mathrm{d}\overrightarrow{r}
I=\int_C\nabla V\cdot\mathrm{d}\overrightarrow{r}=V(b)-V(a)
I=V(2,3)-V(1,0)=-\cos 2+\sin 3+\cos 1
